_About us:_ We’re a Paid Social Ad Creative Agency, that is young, fast-paced, and innovative, working in a variety of different industries.

_What we're looking for:_ A Motion Graphics Designer who is an expert and fast in after effects while having a strong eye for design. You will work closely with our team to design and animate an adbundance of ad creative that drive efficiencies through our clients paid social channels. We love what we do, and we want someone who is positive and open to growth within this industry.

_Type:_ Project to project basis but full-time is a possibility.

_Location:_ Remote

text:
Any content strategists here with a writing/marketing background in climate & sustainability? I'm helping to look for someone who'd be interested in helping out on an ongoing Content Strategy project for Columbia Business School. You'd be working directly with CBS's marketing director as well as a committee of faculty members who focus on climate. More details:
• The goal of the project is to work with faculty to hone a clear CBS message around their work in the climate space (based on faculty research, curricula, alumni successes, etc).
• This ongoing project will require between roughly 5 and 15 hours per week of your time (hours will fluctuate weekly and can be slightly unpredictable).
• The goal is to wrap up the project in late April or early May, but my guess is it will extend longer (again, slightly unpredictable).
• You'd also be working closely with at least two other freelancers who are also working on the project with a focus on different CBS areas; they provide support on the project management piece of the project, and are available for regular check-ins, etc.
• Rates around $100/hr; negotiable based on experience.
If you're interested, please DM me! And let me know if you have any questions
